snippet.textDisplay:
Fun fact, the hyoid is pronounced hi-oi-d (apologies if it doesn't come across well, I'm not great at phonetics lol) and as mark says, it's a small bone in the neck that serves to protect the esophagus and to help anchor the tongue and make speaking possible. It isn't actually articulated to any other bones, which makes it unique. It breaks very rarely without outside pressure on the throat which is why a fracture to the hyoid is most commonly associated with cases of strangulation or hanging.

Anyway, thanks for coming to my random little Ted talk! 😸

snippet.textDisplay:
Hi, public health major here. Myometrium simple means uterine muscle. Myo- muscle, metr- uterus, -ium is a noun ending.
Also, the term fundus isn't exclusive to the uterus. It is simply the part of an organ that is farthest from the opening. A few examples are the bulge at the top of the stomach that goes higher than the esophageal entry point, as well as the retina in the eye.
